    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Reconcile transactions with PostgreSQL and Gmail on autopilot\n\n**Pattern:** Expense Tracking · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Email\n\n## What it does\nReconcile transactions with PostgreSQL and Gmail on autopilot. It reacts to incoming email.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual invoicing is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nOn New Email (Gmail) → Collect Raw Text → Extract Structured Fields → All Required Fields Found? → Upsert into PostgreSQL → Merge Review Paths → Guard Non-Empty amount → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to expense tracking without manual effort\n- Anyone automating invoicing in finance\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Improves response time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2; OpenAI API key; Postgres connection; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "231dbace-d798-fb53-e497-3be6569914d5",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
